  abstract: [
    With the surge of internet penetration, particularly in Indonesia, the needs for consideration of its supporting infrastructure also increases, one of which is the Wi-Fi access point. Therefore, the planning of access point placement to achieve optimal utilization and network coverage has become one of the important stages in building construction. Simulations can be of an assistance and could be done by principle of MoM, FEM, FDTD, and ray tracing with each its own advantages and disadvantages for various conditions and needs. In this study, I as the author developed a GUI application with aim to model radio frequency propagation, especially in common Wi-Fi (IEEE 802.11) frequencies of 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz. The developed algorithm models radio frequency propagation for a 2-dimensional floorplan environment by ray tracing using shooting and bouncing rays (SBR) using geometrical optics (GO) principle with diffraction modelling based on Uniform Theory of Diffraction (UTD) with goal to predict the Received Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI).
  ],
  keywords: (
    "access point",
    "propagation modelling",
    "GUI application",
    "ray tracing",
    "shooting and bouncing rays",
    "RSSI"
  )
)